a. Establish the existence, condition, validity and accuracy of its fixed assets by conducting a physical inventory at least once a year in compliance with    Section 124 of the Manual on NGAS for LGUs, Volume I; and 

b. Expedite the inventory-taking in accordance with the following prescribed procedures:

b.1 Creation of Inventory Committee

A committee shall be formed to take charge of the physical inventory-taking, consisting of two or more employees designated by the head of the agency including the property/ administrative officer or custodian depending on the extent of his accountability. 

b.2 Property Identification and Coding

 Government property shall be properly labeled and identification by the Inventory Committee. Inventory labels of special materials shall contain among others the individual property number to be provided by the corporation concerned. These numbers shall be uniformly printed in India ink, to achieve permanence and best results, and shall be posted on prominent but secure portion of the property for easy identification.
b.3 Acknowledgment Receipt for equipment (ARE)

An officer or employee who receives and is in possession or physical control of the property shall be issued an ARE. Such ARE shall be renewed every three (3) years or every time there is a change in accountability as required by NGAS, Volume II.

b.4 Inventory Reports

The report on the physical count of property, plant and equipment shall be prepared on the prescribed format by the NGAS, Volume II. The report shall be submitted to the Auditor concerned not later than January 31 of each year for the property, plant and equipment.


c. Cause the reconciliation of the inventory reports with the accounting and property records.


